n product is sold less than expected, leading to a less favorable profit outcome.\",2\n1841,\"\"\"SALES PERFORMANCE OF THE BUSINESS\"\"\",\"\"\"The sales performance of the business has been very good over the last year, as shown by the favourable sales quantity variance of $48,144. Overall, total revenue is 33% higher than budgeted due to an increase in the total number of valets performed. The number of mini valets increased dramatically by 99%, while full valets increased by 11%. The adverse sales mix variance of $6,554 is reflective of changes in consumer behavior due to decreased disposable incomes and longer car retention periods.\"\"\",2\n1840,\"\"\"TOTAL SALES QUANTITY CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Total sales quantity contribution variance = (actual sales quantity in budgeted proportions - budgeted sales quantity) * standard contribution per unit.\"\"\",2\n1838,\"\"\"STANDARD CONTRIBUTION PER UNIT\"\"\",\"\"\"Standard contribution per unit for Full valet = $50 * 44.6% = $22.30 per valet; for Mini valet = $30 * 55% = $16.50 per valet.\"\"\",2\n1839,\"\"\"TOTAL SALES MIX CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Total sales mix contribution variance = (actual sales quantity - actual sales quantity in budgeted proportions) * standard contribution per unit.\"\"\",1\n\n\n-----Relationships-----\nhuman_readable_id,source,target,description,rank\n830,\"\"\"VARIANCE ANALYSIS\"\"\",\"\"\"SALES PERFORMANCE FOR THE YEAR\"\"\",\"\"\"Variance analysis is used to understand the sales performance for the year.\"\"\",15\n1415,\"\"\"SALES QUANTITY CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"MATERIALS MIX VARIANCE STATEMENTS\"\"\",\"\"\"Both quizzes involve variances related to sales and production processes, specifically quantity and mix variances.\"\"\",8\n1416,\"\"\"SALES QUANTITY CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"SALES MIX CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Sales mix contribution variance and sales quantity contribution variance both measure the effect on profit of changes in sales mix